parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Reverse Gear in ZF 5HP19 Transmission
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the reverse gear can cause the vehicle to suddenly lose the ability to reverse, leading to potential accidents or near-misses, especially when reversing out of driveways or parking spaces.
symptoms: The vehicle refuses to engage in reverse gear
the vehicle will only move in reverse at idle on a flat surface but will not accelerate
the transmission fails without warning while driving

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the airbag system can lead to unexpected airbag deployment, which can cause injuries or distractions while driving, or failure to deploy in the event of a crash, which can increase the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: airbags fail to deploy in the event of a crash
injuries or near-misses due to airbag malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the radiator fan can cause loud noises, excessive current draw, and battery drain, leading to overheating, engine failure, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The radiator fan makes a loud noise
draws current even when the engine is off
and may result in repeated battery replacements.
